### 10. Backward Compatibility and Migration

**localStorage migration:** Old values `"light"`, `"dark"`, `"system"` are automatically mapped to `"t3-light"`, `"t3-dark"`, `"system"` by the `migrateStoredTheme` function. The stored value is NOT re-written on read (only on next explicit `setTheme`), preventing unnecessary side effects.

**Cross-tab sync:** The `storage` event listener continues to work. When one tab changes the theme, all tabs pick up the new `ThemeName` and apply it.

**Tailwind `dark:` prefix:** Because themes with `base: "dark"` apply the `.dark` class on `<html>`, all existing `dark:bg-*`, `dark:text-*`, `not-dark:*` utilities continue to work correctly. `t3-midnight` is dark-based, so `.dark` is present and Tailwind dark variants activate.

