### 4. Refactored `useTheme` Hook (`apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts`)

The hook must:
- Store `ThemeName` (including `"system"`) in localStorage under the same key `"t3code:theme"` for backward compatibility
- Apply the resolved theme's `.dark` class for Tailwind compatibility
- Apply theme-specific CSS variable overrides as inline styles on `document.documentElement`
- Clear previously applied overrides when switching themes
- Expose `resolvedTheme: "light" | "dark"` for `DiffWorkerPoolProvider`, `DiffPanel`, `ChatMarkdown`, `ChatView`
- Maintain the `useSyncExternalStore` pattern and cross-tab sync
- Handle migration: if localStorage contains `"light"` or `"dark"` (old values), map them to `"t3-light"` or `"t3-dark"`

#### Key implementation details:

**Migration of stored values:**
```typescript
function migrateStoredTheme(raw: string | null): ThemeName {
  if (raw === "light") return "t3-light";
  if (raw === "dark") return "t3-dark";
  if (raw === "system") return "system";
  if (raw !== null && isThemeName(raw)) return raw;
  return "system";  // default
}
```

**Applying CSS variables:**

Track which CSS variables were last set so they can be removed when switching:

```typescript
let appliedCssVarKeys: string[] = [];

function applyCssVars(colors: ThemeColors): void {
  const el = document.documentElement;
  // Remove previously applied overrides
  for (const key of appliedCssVarKeys) {
    el.style.removeProperty(`--${key}`);
  }
  // Apply new overrides
  const nextKeys: string[] = [];
  for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(colors)) {
    if (value !== undefined) {
      el.style.setProperty(`--${key}`, value);
      nextKeys.push(key);
    }
  }
  appliedCssVarKeys = nextKeys;
}
```

**The `applyTheme` function refactored:**
```typescript
function applyTheme(themeName: ThemeName, suppressTransitions = false): void {
  if (suppressTransitions) {
    document.documentElement.classList.add("no-transitions");
  }

  const prefersDark = getSystemDark();
  const resolved = resolveTheme(themeName, prefersDark);

  // Toggle .dark class based on theme base
  document.documentElement.classList.toggle("dark", resolved.base === "dark");

  // Apply CSS custom property overrides
  applyCssVars(resolved.colors);

  if (suppressTransitions) {
    document.documentElement.offsetHeight; // force reflow
    requestAnimationFrame(() => {
      document.documentElement.classList.remove("no-transitions");
    });
  }
}
```

**Hook return type remains backward-compatible:**
```typescript
export function useTheme() {
  // ... useSyncExternalStore as before, but snapshot includes ThemeName
  return {
    theme: snapshot.theme,            // ThemeName (was Theme)
    setTheme,                         // (next: ThemeName) => void
    resolvedTheme,                    // "light" | "dark" (unchanged contract)
    resolvedThemeDefinition,          // ThemeDefinition (new, for UI)
  } as const;
}
```

The `resolvedTheme` property is derived from `resolvedThemeDefinition.base`, so `DiffWorkerPoolProvider`, `ChatMarkdown`, `ChatView`, and `DiffPanel` all continue to receive `"light" | "dark"` without any code changes.

**Type export for consumers:**

The old `type Theme = "light" | "dark" | "system"` is replaced by importing `ThemeName` from `@t3tools/shared/theme`. All internal references remain compatible.

